## ðŸ›ï¸ Landmark Trials & 2026 Legal Status

### **1. TotalEnergies: The French Duty of Vigilance Trial**

* **Current Status:** **Live Hearings (Feb 19â€“20, 2026).** A historic trial is currently underway in Paris. For the first time, judges are deciding if a multinational can be legally forced to stop fossil fuel expansion (specifically targeting projects like EACOP in Uganda/Tanzania) to meet climate goals.
* **The Goal:** Plaintiffs (Sherpa, Friends of the Earth, and the City of Paris) are demanding a **37% reduction in oil production** by 2030.
* **Resource:** [Sherpaâ€™s Case Archive](https://www.asso-sherpa.org) | [#StopEACOP Official Website](https://www.stopeacop.net)

### **2. Shell: The "Legacy Pollution" Victory**

* **Current Status:** **Upcoming Merits Trial (March 2027).** In June 2025, the UK High Court delivered a massive win for the Bille and Ogale communities, ruling that Shell PLC **can be held liable** for "legacy pollution" dating back decades, regardless of current ownership or "sabotage" claims.
* **Key Finding:** The judge ruled that failing to clean up an old oil spill is a **"continuous breach"** of law, allowing victims to sue years after the initial damage.
* **Resource:** [Leigh Day - Shell Nigeria Cases](https://www.leighday.co.uk) | [Amnesty International - Niger Delta](https://www.amnesty.org)

### **3. Glencore: Individual Accountability**

* **Current Status:** **Criminal Pleas (Nov 2025 â€“ Feb 2026).** While Glencore paid $1.3B in corporate fines in 2022, the focus has shifted to its leaders. In late 2025, former top traders pleaded "not guilty" to bribery charges in West Africa. A full criminal trial is scheduled for **October 2027**.
* **Resource:** [SFO Glencore Investigation](https://www.sfo.gov.uk) | [Corruption Watch DRC](https://www.corruptionwatch.org.za)

